sql:
SELECT DISTINCT threads.thread_id, threads.thread_title, threads.creation_datetime, threads.category_id, threads.language, threads.location
FROM threads
WHERE threads.author_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
- "contributors" refers to the users who have made posts; 
- "languages used in their threads" refers to the languages of the threads they have contributed to; 
- "total count of their contributions" means the number of posts they have made;
- "general mood of their posts" corresponds to the average sentiment score of their posts, indicating whether the posts are generally positive, neutral, or negative.

sql:
SELECT thread_title
FROM threads
WHERE thread_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "Most active users" in a category are those who have contributed a significant number of threads, posts, and views in the recently created threads of that category;
- "Locked threads" refer to threads that cannot be further discussed or modified;
- "Pinned threads" are threads that are fixed at the top of the category page;
- "Ranking of the categories" is determined by the number of threads within each category;
- User activity is measured by the number of threads and posts they have contributed.

sql:
SELECT thread_title 
FROM threads 
WHERE author_id = (SELECT user_id FROM users WHERE username = 'User123');

external_knowledge:
Prolific posters are defined as users who have contributed more than 100 posts;
Personal info of the authors includes their username and email;
Posts are considered prolific based on the frequency of their contributions.

sql:
SELECT threads.thread_id, categories.category_name
FROM threads
JOIN categories ON threads.category_id = categories.category_id;

external_knowledge:
- "gardeners" refer to the users who started threads; 
- "seeds" are analogies for the threads they created; 
- "digital garden" means the online discussion platform; 
- "year of the Water Tiger" is an indirect reference to the year 2022; 
- "blossoms" represent the threads that received responses or posts; 
- "more than one response" indicates threads that have more than one post; 
- "abundance of their cultivation efforts" refers to threads with high numbers of posts.

- 'Unaltered posts' refers to posts that have not been edited (is_edited = 0);
- 'Pinned discussions' are threads that are pinned to the top (is_pinned = 1);
- 'Relevant to Japan' means the location tag for the thread is set to Japan;
- 'Strength of their sentiments' refers to the sentiment score, with higher scores indicating stronger sentiments.

- "areas of discussion" refers to categories in the forum;
- "generated the highest buzz" means the categories with the most posts;
- "how many posts they've accumulated" corresponds to the count of posts per category.

sql:
SELECT thread_id, view_region, AVG(view_count) AS average_view_count
FROM thread_views
GROUP BY thread_id, view_region;
